title: Tales from Viking Times by Magnus Magnusson
description:
Author: Magnus Magnusson
Title: Tales from Viking Times
Source: Audio cassette
Released: 1981 Music for Pleasure: TC-LFP 80165-6
Digitized in Audacity
Format: mp3
Bit rate: 160 kbps
Running time: 1 hour 56 minutes


From the back cover:

"In this personal selection of stories, Magnus Magnusson, himself a descendant of the Vikings tells the Tales from Viking times he grew up with, ranging from folk tales about elves and fairies and ghosts to the great Sagas of heroism and high drama involving Viking champions and their gods."

From Wikipedia:

Magnus Magnusson was a tv presenter, journalist and writer. He was born in Iceland but lived in Scotland for most of his life.

Rippers note: An enjoyable introduction to the Viking sagas. Occasional squashiness due to old tapes.
